\f1\b0 \cf0 \
Tsugi is software library written in PHP that allows a wide range of educational software and content to be seamlessly plugged into Learning Management Systems like Sakai, Canvas, Coursera, Blackboard, Moodle, and Desire2Learn.\
\
Tsugi supports all the major IMS integrations standards including LTI Advantage, Deep Linking, Common Cartridge and others.  Tsugi also supports Google Classroom.\
\
The Tsugi library has been used by open source projects like Xerte and Curriki, and commercial projects like SchoolCity.\
\
Because Tsugi is a rich implementation and written in PHP (making it easy to install and host), Tsugi played an essential role in the early interoperability testing between the various LMS vendors as they built their initial LTI Advantage implementations.  Four of the five major LMS providers shipped certified LTI Advantage support at the same time as the standard was released - in 2019 in part because of the work done by Tsugi.\
\
Many LTI Tool vendors have used Tsugi to help understand the LTI Advantage specification by comparing their code to the working implementation in Tsugi.\
\
Tsugi continues to be at the core of evolving IMS standards as a free, open, and easy to understand reference implementation.  Tsugi can quickly be extended to test out new prototype ideas for specifications and then help insure interoperability between LMSs with a new specification.\
\
The www.tsugicloud.org and Dayton Tsugi installations show how Tsugi can be used to provide an application store for education.  The tsugicloud.org app store has over 20 applications, mostly developed by the University of Dayton or me.\
\
Python for Everybody (www.py4e.com) supports the largest programming course in the world.  Using Tsugi and LTI it is deployed on Coursera, edX, and Futurelearn and in use by over 300 schools around the world to support teaching Python.  Each school gets their own key and uses LTI and Common Cartridge to make use of the materials in the PY4E learning object repository.\
