\f1\b0 \cf0 \
As the pandemic moved so many schools online I thought there would be an increased demand for innovative assessment tools   So I quickly wrote tools like Document Annotator using CKEditor and StickyGrader (PDF + Stickies).   I thought folks wanted innovative tools for assessments during the pandemic - but really they mostly wanted to use the same stuff they always had used and complain about it :)  There was just not enough energy among my colleagues to try something new.\
\
Another major tool development was a threaded discussion tool.  This tool is important because it is the last core function of an LMS that was missing for Tsugi.  With the addition of a discussion tool, Tsugi can be used as a very simple stand alone LMS.  What is missing is now a simple way to author courses.\
\
I invested in documentation and software to make self-hosting of Tsugi easier.  I gave instructions and scripts to host a simple school on DigitalOcean and showed how to deploy a more scalable solution using Amazon Web Services.\
\
Also work has started on experimental support for PostgreSQL.\
